article.linkText: Wright scores 16 to lift Princeton past Penn 74-64
article.story: PRINCETON, N.J. -- — Ethan Wright had 16 points as Princeton won its ninth straight game, defeating Penn 74-64 on Monday. Matt Allocco had 12 points for Princeton (14-3, 4-0 Ivy League). Jaelin Llewellyn added 11 points and Drew Friberg had 10 points. Jelani Williams had 13 points for the Quakers (6-12, 3-2). Michael Moshkovitz added 12 points, Clark Slajchert had 10 points, and George Smith had nine points and 10 rebounds. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
